HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1066
By Warner
A RESOLUTION to honor H. Dean Delk on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those estimable public servants whose lives exemplify dedicated service,
integrity, and commitment to the people of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, H. Dean Delk has rendered exemplary service to the citizens of Marshall
County, serving as a county commissioner for an extraordinary twenty-eight years, from 1998
through 2026, during which time he demonstrated steadfast leadership, sound judgment, and an
unwavering commitment to the public good; and
WHEREAS, prior to and concurrent with his public service, Mr. Delk devoted his
professional career to the education of Tennessee's youth, serving with distinction as principal
of Forrest High School from 1985 to 1996, where he fostered academic excellence, discipline,
and character development; and
WHEREAS, he continued his educational leadership as principal of Chapel Hill
Elementary School from 1996 until 2014, leaving a lasting legacy of mentorship, student
advocacy, and institutional growth that benefited generations of students and families; and
WHEREAS, H. Dean Delk has consistently extended his service beyond his professional
obligations through active civic and charitable involvement, including membership in the Chapel
Hill Lions Club, volunteer service with Special Olympics, and steadfast advocacy on behalf of
veterans and their families; and
WHEREAS, further exemplifying his devotion to duty and country, Mr. Delk honorably
served as a major in the Tennessee Army National Guard, providing leadership and service in
support of both State and national missions; and
HJR1066
014061
- 1 -

WHEREAS, throughout his career in education, public office, military service, and
community engagement, H. Dean Delk has embodied the highest ideals of public service,
earning the respect, gratitude, and admiration of colleagues, students, and citizens alike; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Delk is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service that
have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and he should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and commend H. Dean Delk for his decades of
distinguished service to the State of Tennessee, extend our sincere appreciation for his lasting
contributions to education, public service, and community life, and wish him continued health,
fulfillment, and success in all future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
